<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="426" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,756,1014,1324]" lastBlockId="35.[831,1436,258,315]" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1014,1037]" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Small to medium-sized spiders (carapace length of males 4.42-6.46, carapace width 4.02- 5.87). Distinguished from species of other groups by males with a strongly reduced proximal edge on the tegulum (
<figureCitation box="[259,367,1141,1165]" captionStart="Fig. 19" captionStartId="37.[151,186,1883,1904]" captionTargetBox="[158,1437,494,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[148,1448,467,1845]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Liphistius batuensis, details of left palp of two males from type locality: specimen collected 24. VII. 1969 (A-B, F, I), specimen matured 8. II. 2002 (C-E, G-H). (A) Distal part of palp (palpal organ not indicated), ventral view. (B) Paracymbium, retrolateral view. (C) Distal part of cymbium, prolateral view. (D) Palpal organ, distal view (dorsal side up; arrow indicating proventral angle at base of para-embolic plate). (E) Palpal organ, proventral view (arrow indicating same structure as in D). (F) Embolus complex, proventral view. (G) Palpal organ, retroventral and slightly proximal view (arrow indicating same structure as in D-E). (H) Same, retrodorsal view. (I) Same, prolateral view. Abbreviation: T - tegulum. Scale lines: 1.0 mm (A, C; B) and 0.5 mm (D-I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021977/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">Figs 19H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[383,431,1141,1165]" captionStart="Fig. 21" captionStartId="40.[151,186,1796,1817]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,264,1742]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[148,1446,254,1764]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Fig. 21. Liphistius tempurung, details of left palp of four males: specimen from type locality, matured 13. XI. 2005 (A-F, I); from Gua Cicak, matured 23. I. 2005 (G, J); from type locality, matured 26. IX. 2004 (H, K); from type locality, matured 25. IX. 2004 (L). (A) Cymbium and palpal organ, ventral view. (B) Palpal organ, retrodorsal and slightly distal view. (C) Distal margin of cymbium and palpal organ, prolateral view. (D) Paracymbium, retrolateral view. (E) Distal part of palpal tibia, ventral view. (F) Tibial apophysis, retrodorsal and slightly proximal view. (G) Same, retrolateral and slightly proximal view. (H) Distal part of cymbium, prolateral view. (I-L) Palpal organ, distal view (dorsal side up). Abbreviations: T - tegulum; vp - ventral process of contrategulum. Scale lines: 0.5 mm (A, D-G; B-C, H-L)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021981/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">21B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[447,484,1141,1165]" captionStart="Fig. 23" captionStartId="44.[147,182,1855,1876]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,261,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[148,1439,254,1807]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="Fig. 23. Liphistius priceae sp. nov., details of palp of six males; holotype (A-D, H-K), male paratype collected mature (E), paratype matured 20. VII. 2004 (F), paratype matured 1. VIII. 2004 (G), paratype matured 18. IX. 2004 (L-M) and paratype matured 11. VIII. 2005 (N-O). (A) Left cymbium and palpal organ, ventral view. (B) Distal part of left tibia, ventral view. (C) Left paracymbium, retrolateral view. (D-E) Left palpal organ, distal view (dorsal side up). (F-G) Dorsal apex of contrategulum of right palpal organ, distal view (dorsal side to the left). (H) Distal part of left palpal organ, prolateral view. (I) Same, retrodorsal and slightly distal view. (J) Distal part of cymbium, prolateral view. (K-L, N) Left tibial apophysis, retrolateral and slightly proximal view. (M, O) Right tibial apophysis, same view. Abbreviations: T - tegulum; vp - ventral process of contrategulum. Scale lines: 1.0 mm (A-C, K-O), 0.5 mm (D-I; J)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021987/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">
<date box="[447,484,1141,1165]" pageId="35" pageNumber="426" value="1923-01">23I</date>
</figureCitation>
) and with an elongated prodorsal-apical lobe on the cymbium (
<figureCitation box="[586,689,1172,1197]" captionStart="Fig. 19" captionStartId="37.[151,186,1883,1904]" captionTargetBox="[158,1437,494,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[148,1448,467,1845]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Liphistius batuensis, details of left palp of two males from type locality: specimen collected 24. VII. 1969 (A-B, F, I), specimen matured 8. II. 2002 (C-E, G-H). (A) Distal part of palp (palpal organ not indicated), ventral view. (B) Paracymbium, retrolateral view. (C) Distal part of cymbium, prolateral view. (D) Palpal organ, distal view (dorsal side up; arrow indicating proventral angle at base of para-embolic plate). (E) Palpal organ, proventral view (arrow indicating same structure as in D). (F) Embolus complex, proventral view. (G) Palpal organ, retroventral and slightly proximal view (arrow indicating same structure as in D-E). (H) Same, retrodorsal view. (I) Same, prolateral view. Abbreviation: T - tegulum. Scale lines: 1.0 mm (A, C; B) and 0.5 mm (D-I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021977/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">Figs 19C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[703,751,1173,1197]" captionStart="Fig. 21" captionStartId="40.[151,186,1796,1817]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,264,1742]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[148,1446,254,1764]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Fig. 21. Liphistius tempurung, details of left palp of four males: specimen from type locality, matured 13. XI. 2005 (A-F, I); from Gua Cicak, matured 23. I. 2005 (G, J); from type locality, matured 26. IX. 2004 (H, K); from type locality, matured 25. IX. 2004 (L). (A) Cymbium and palpal organ, ventral view. (B) Palpal organ, retrodorsal and slightly distal view. (C) Distal margin of cymbium and palpal organ, prolateral view. (D) Paracymbium, retrolateral view. (E) Distal part of palpal tibia, ventral view. (F) Tibial apophysis, retrodorsal and slightly proximal view. (G) Same, retrolateral and slightly proximal view. (H) Distal part of cymbium, prolateral view. (I-L) Palpal organ, distal view (dorsal side up). Abbreviations: T - tegulum; vp - ventral process of contrategulum. Scale lines: 0.5 mm (A, D-G; B-C, H-L)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021981/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">21H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,193,1205,1229]" captionStart="Fig. 23" captionStartId="44.[147,182,1855,1876]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,261,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[148,1439,254,1807]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="Fig. 23. Liphistius priceae sp. nov., details of palp of six males; holotype (A-D, H-K), male paratype collected mature (E), paratype matured 20. VII. 2004 (F), paratype matured 1. VIII. 2004 (G), paratype matured 18. IX. 2004 (L-M) and paratype matured 11. VIII. 2005 (N-O). (A) Left cymbium and palpal organ, ventral view. (B) Distal part of left tibia, ventral view. (C) Left paracymbium, retrolateral view. (D-E) Left palpal organ, distal view (dorsal side up). (F-G) Dorsal apex of contrategulum of right palpal organ, distal view (dorsal side to the left). (H) Distal part of left palpal organ, prolateral view. (I) Same, retrodorsal and slightly distal view. (J) Distal part of cymbium, prolateral view. (K-L, N) Left tibial apophysis, retrolateral and slightly proximal view. (M, O) Right tibial apophysis, same view. Abbreviations: T - tegulum; vp - ventral process of contrategulum. Scale lines: 1.0 mm (A-C, K-O), 0.5 mm (D-I; J)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021987/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">23J</figureCitation>
). Females similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peter J. Schwendinger" authorityYear="2017" box="[583,652,1204,1227]" class="Arachnida" family="Liphistiidae" genus="Liphistius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="35" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linang">
<emphasis box="[583,652,1204,1227]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">linang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group in possessing a vulval plate with reduced pigmentation and sclerotisation, distinguished by a relatively wider vulval plate with the poreplate only partially connected to the large and wide posterior stalk or separated by a short distance (
<figureCitation box="[933,1016,290,315]" captionStart="Fig. 20" captionStartId="38.[151,186,1993,2014]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,578,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[148,1439,556,1950]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Fig. 20. Liphistius batuensis, vulval plate of five females from the type locality: exuvia, moult 24. I. 2002 (A-B); specimen SMF 13907 (C); exuvia, moult 12. VII. 2001 (D-E); specimen leg. XI. 1976 (F); exuvia, moult 13. I. 2002 (G-H). (A, C-D, F-G) Dorsal view. (B, E, H) Ventral view. Scale lines: 1.0 mm (A-B, D-E, G-H; C, F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021979/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">Figs 20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1027,1056,291,315]" captionStart="Fig. 22" captionStartId="41.[147,182,1789,1810]" captionTargetBox="[153,1429,258,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[148,1446,254,1752]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 22. Liphistius tempurung, details of copulatory organ and genital sternite of six females: Gua Cicak, specimen moulted 8. I. 2005 (A- B, N); Gua Tempurung, exuvia, moult 22. I. 2007 (C-D, M); Gua Tempurung, exuvia, moult 9. XII. 2004 (E-F); Gua Tempurung, exuvia, moult 21. X. 2004 (G-H); medium-sized female from Gua Cicak (I-J); small female from Gua Tempurung (K-L). (A, C, E, G, I, K) Vulval plate, dorsal view. (B, D, F, H) Same, ventral view. (J, L) Receptacular cluster, ventral view. (M-N) Posterior margin of genital sternite, ventral view. Scale lines: 1.0 mm (A-D, I-L; E-H; M-N)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021985/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1067,1097,291,315]" captionStart="Fig. 24" captionStartId="45.[149,184,1333,1354]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,263,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[148,1446,254,1296]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 24. Liphistius priceae sp. nov., vulval plate of four female paratypes (all from exuviae): paratype, moult 1. I. 2006 (A-B), allotype, moult 24. XI. 2004 (C-D), paratype, moult 13. XI. 2005 (E), paratype, moult 2. IV. 2005 (F). (A, C, E-F) Dorsal view. (B) Lateral view. (D) Ventral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm (A-F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1021989/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[831,1437,337,393]" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,1035,337,360]" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">Species included:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abraham" authorityYear="1923" box="[1047,1267,337,360]" class="Arachnida" family="Liphistiidae" genus="Liphistius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="35" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batuensis">
<emphasis box="[1047,1267,337,360]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">Liphistius batuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1437,338,361]" class="Arachnida" family="Liphistiidae" genus="Liphistius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="35" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tempurung">
<emphasis box="[1286,1437,338,361]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="426">L. tempurung</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Peter J. Schwendinger, 2017" authorityName="Peter J. Schwendinger" authorityYear="2017" box="[877,985,370,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Liphistiidae" genus="Liphistius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="35" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="priceae" status="sp. nov.">
